The Sales department generates revenue and powers our organization forward. We keep up with the latest sales trends and technology incorporate them into our daily work and keep in touch with each other for better results. Main Responsibilities 

Revenue Strategy: Develop and oversee a clear channel development strategy with focus on distribution and in alignment with Nord Layer’s business objectives;
Identify market trends partner needs and competitive insights to shape effective sales strategy through partners;
Collaborate with strategic partners and distributors to set revenue targets and KPIs and deliver execution plans to reach them;
Focus all energy and efforts towards achieving the monthly sales goals through strategic initiatives and team enablement;

Partnerships and Alliances: Cultivate and nurture strong relationships with distributors and key partners understanding their needs addressing concerns and providing tailored solutions that align with their business objectives;
Identify potential strategic partnerships alliances and distribution channels to expand channel sales;
Lead negotiations with partners finalize agreements and manage contracts to establish mutually beneficial terms that drive sales growth and brand presence;

Sales and Marketing Alignment: Foster collaboration and alignment between the sales and marketing teams to maximize lead generation and conversion through strategic partners and distributors;
Oversee the development of sales and marketing strategies to optimize customer acquisition and retention;
Oversee sales promotions evaluate their effectiveness and success and make data-driven decisions to optimize future promotions;

Team Leadership: Build and lead a high-performing channel sales team;
Provide mentorship guidance and support to team members. Core Requirements  

Sales Leadership Experience: A minimum of 5 years in senior sales roles preferably within the Cybersecurity industry showcasing a consistent record of leading successful sales teams and finalizing crucial contracts;

Strategic Vision: Demonstrated ability to develop and implement strategic sales plans identifying and seizing upon market opportunities. Proven adaptability to navigate dynamic market landscapes leading teams through periods of growth and transformation;

Industry Knowledge: Familiarity with Cybersecurity IT or related sectors understanding SaaS business models particularly in driving growth through Channel sales strategies;

Relationship Management: Exceptional interpersonal skills with a proven ability to build and maintain long-term relationships pivotal for sustained business success;

Negotiation Skills: Strong negotiation and contract management abilities adept at closing deals and creating win-win outcomes.

Analytical Acumen: Demonstrated expertise in analyzing sales data and market trends and interpreting performance metrics to drive well-informed decision-making processes. interpreting performance metrics to drive well-informed decision-making processes;

Hands-on approach: strong growth mindset proactive and hands-on attitude helping the team to develop the channel. Salary Range 
We are open to discuss salaries based on your skills. The bonuses will be paid based on the results achieved. Additional Information 
About Us
Nord Security is a global leader in internet privacy and security solutions and Lithuania’s second tech unicorn. Established in 2012 Nord Security now has more than 1400 employees and serves millions of users worldwide. Our team has a global mission to shape a more secure and peaceful online future for people everywhere.
With that in mind we built 4 advanced cybersecurity solutions: NordVPN NordLayer NordLocker and NordPass.
NordLayer is an adaptive network access security solution for modern businesses developed by the standard of NordVPN.
We help organizations of all sizes enhance their internet security and modernize network and resource access with technical improvements aligning with the best regulatory compliance standards. Helping organizations to adopt ZTNA principles NordLayer is focused on the Security Service Edge of cybersecurity services.
Quick and easy to integrate with existing infrastructure hardware-free and designed with ease of scale in mind NordLayer meets the varying growth pace and ad-hoc cybersecurity requirements of agile businesses and distributed workforces today.
And we’re always looking to expand our team of :
• Future shapers
• Restless achievers
• Self-movers
• Honest communicators
• Team players
What We Offer
• Access to Nord Security products. We build solutions used by millions of users worldwide and you’ll get to experience our products firsthand;
