Working in Communications means contributing to the value creation of Nord products and Nord Security as a whole. We recognize the value of expressing our organization’s stance through content development and media activity. Our reputation is built on our ability to deliver quickly think creatively and outside the box and approach challenges with a positive and results-oriented attitude. 
Nord Security is a home for advanced security solutions used by millions of customers worldwide. Our products are known for the use of cutting-edge technologies attention to clients’ needs and strongly held values. We aim to become one of the most trusted privacy and security service providers in the world. 
The Brand Communications 
team ensures that everyone inside and outside of Nord Security knows what takes place in our company. The team takes care of internal and external brand communications channels: from newsletters website internal & external events to social media and external media channels executes employer brand communications plans aligns marketing campaigns establishes brand awareness and builds online reputation. Main Responsibilities 
Manage video content creation and production process (from creative brief to final video) for different online and offline platforms such as TV Youtube social media channels and website;
Ensure brand consistency in video content by ensuring tone of voice messaging and visual identity is in place;
Drive SEO and advertising best practices incorporation into editorial video workflow (make sure that the video fits specific channels requirements);
Collaborate with other departments to produce videos - scriptwriters designers illustrators;
Improve and revamp existing video content delivery processes to reduce costs and increase efficiency;
Listen to and understand the stakeholder needs related to the video project - and help translate related solutions into the video projects;
Collaborate with the stakeholder to ensure a project staff that will help ensure quality deliverables for the stakeholder on time and within budget;
Effectively communicate project expectations to team members and stakeholders;
Work with other project managers to manage and prioritize competing deadlines and tasks;
Create and manage detailed project plans ensuring that all deliverables are tracked for on time delivery to the stakeholders;
Review project deliverables providing quality assurance in line with project scope and objectives;
Quickly identify and escalate issues dependencies or risks to team goals or project timelines;
Advocate both the creative and commercial value of delivery across the business and build strong relationships with colleagues globally to ensure toolkits are created to be accessible and malleable for all market needs. Core Requirements  
At least 3+ years of hands-on experience in leading video content projects from the concept idea to execution in the following industries: marketing digital advertising or commercial video production;
Demonstrated deep understanding of communication and marketing strategies with a proven track record of successful implementation in previous roles;
Having strong creative instincts and will thrive off working with creatives editors and production experts have an excellent eye for craft and storytelling in moving images and be constantly curious about cultural and viewing trends along with emerging visual styles;
In-depth understanding of the video creation and production processes;
Excellent organizational and planning skills;
Excellent written and verbal communication skills in both internal and stakeholder-facing settings across all levels of an organization;
Sharp attention to detail and organizational skills to keep projects on deadline and budget;
Monitor stakeholder’s relationship and project status to identify any areas of risk or issue;
Makes sound well-informed and objective decisions for the business stakeholders and team members;
Willingness to train and mentor less-experienced team members;
Ambition to shape the future of a fast-growing in-house video production team;
A degree in Marketing Project Management or video-related experience when working with brands or agencies. Salary Range 
